      <div class="about_head">THE<br> FACE HAUS<br> STORY</div>
      <p>After a facial birthday party that broke the bank, good friends and busy, working moms Karey Burke, Dawn
        Olmstead and Jenn Worley went on the hunt for a great facial that they could afford on the regular.&nbsp; They
        couldn’t find what they were looking for- so they built it.</p>
      <p>The powerhouse trio envisioned a place where men, women &amp; teens could get fantastic, spa-grade facials
        without all the fuss (adios private, dark rooms and Peruvian flute music). A fun, fresh, modern destination
        with an upbeat attitude and an uplifting message of inclusion.&nbsp; The goal? A&nbsp;no-compromise accessible
        facial.</p>
      <p>They created a service menu with celebrity dermatologist Dr. Harold Lancer, hired a team of superstar
        estheticians, and brought their light-bulb moment to life. The first Face Haus launched in Los Angeles in
        2013, and the brand hasn’t stopped growing—or glowing—since.</p>
    </div>
    <div id="abt_3" class="about_texts" style="display: none;">
